== Introduction ==
A plugin for OpenDaylight SAL to be capable of communicating with generic commodity Ethernet switch.
== Release Deliverables ==
{|class="wikitable"
! Name
! Description
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Basic RW
| Implementation for OpenDaylight SAL API of basic switch reading/writing functions (such as sal.proprogrammer and sal.reader). Switch table could be modified using SNMP.
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Full RW
| Implementation for OpenDaylight SAL API of listening to switch events (such as sal.inventory). Events or status changes of the switch could be received (with SNMP trap) so as to react in the plugin.
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Completed
| Implementation for all OpenDaylight SAL API (except for the APIs incompatible with generic commodity Ethernet switches)
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Extended
| Implementation for extended OpenDaylight SAL API (such as disabling STP and disabling flooding)
|}

